SUMMARY AND DIAGNOSIS
======================================================================

  Most likely causes of sigma_x inflation (ranked):

  See diagnostics above:
  1. If best_phase_offset diagnostic removes most tangential RMSE:
       => Layer 1 tau drift / phase misalignment is primary cause
  2. If tau_hint gives lower RMSE than tau_mean (G < H or F < E):
       => Layer 1 boundary sampling moves tau away from true boundaries
  3. If baseline B–A gap >> 0 and > 50% of total surplus RMSE:
       => Single-sample noisy anchor is contributing
  4. If center forced to 0 gives lower RMSE (G < F or H < E):
       => center compensation is harmful for clean data
  5. If divergences concentrate in c_k or z regions:
       => geometry of center/z coupling needs reparameterization

  Recommended next model change (do not implement — diagnostics only):
  If tau drift is primary: consider fixing tau to tau_hint in Layer 2,
  or adding a tighter tau prior / passing tau_hint directly to Layer 2.
